[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering build options**\n\nI'm thinking about altering the test task by adjusting the jvmArgs to place the installer module on the module path and adding necessary modules. My concern is that the system classloader might find the module before the classpath does. I could also explore adding a doFirst task in build.gradle to create the jar, but that might not be a good idea. The user wants tests only under the source root, so I'll avoid modifying build.gradle.\n\n**Considering installation strategies**\n\nI'm pondering whether to remove the failing named installer assertion and rely on a different branch. Although, line 156 is still uncovered, which is not ideal. I think it might be helpful to call `ClassReloadingStrategy.fromInstalledAgent` from a dynamically built full module. Perhaps using a copied `Installer` in the same module could be the key if `loadClass` successfully returns the copied class from there.\n\n**Considering test forks**\n\nI'm thinking about whether to run tests in the same fork. If I set `forkEvery=1`, does that mean there'll be one test class per fork? I wonder if I can include multiple methods within the same class, even if the Installer isn't loaded. Also, I need to consider how to handle situations where the classpath isn't loaded by the dynamic access agent. Hmm, I think I might need to patch that part.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_080a077674b6d198016a29483d586c8190a545103a0175a968\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKUhyMaCsvSyz0MSzLcCZUTmhW0bqgy6TbEP3ImPHmv92D9ykhiULnFuHlYWi-y1zACE1jiC3IUlxN0puGEitHS7yLh2dAzPrL36wu1XXQuy96HUBvX3C6kOJypeowUmgQ1J_jEsSOBelr9-nm8OmTupw2UrG4m7i8VadS52kNwoAyEj-PDH1hzd_hby48Sxr1tfuydS4BFYF86UmJ97u-sqqmJ94CpFVWQ9tqx97N9XU5BREX6NK3CxTijbZ8SQoZFyoznXj0OsKCxOBNUXUJLLTBV2fwvbb2TybycrXTE-6uVGAQSpvGhUVd1xGj0Hcpo1REuHpanQA65pHhMDGceraXoVUfqu9oTz8sJEeG7EfIRKQB57VLvE